      {
        "id" : "01bf3f97-a640-4862-b0bd-5d694ec42d72",
        "parentId" : "248ea149-f030-4adf-b469-88d375f89e7f",
        "authorId" : "6eca0ade-9879-4dd7-ad14-547e16f5c041",
        "body" : "I find this really strange that clients need to delete each version of a collection.  Isn't the resource the same independent of its version from a storage perspective?  Why do I feel like this is confusing the concept of version with distinct fundamental identity?  Doesn't every version of the object share the same fundamental uid?  Are they not the same resource at the end of the day?\n",
        "createdAt" : "2016-11-17T14:56:11Z",
        "updatedAt" : "2016-11-18T22:32:24Z",
        "lastEditedBy" : "6eca0ade-9879-4dd7-ad14-547e16f5c041",
        "tags" : [
